{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "They pay lavish fees to manage their wealth, while tuition keeps rising.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by Prof Victor Fleischer criticizes American universities for using their tax-exempt endowments for investment rather than tuition assistance or expansion of faculty research; observes Yale paid far more in 2014 for private equity fees than it did in tuition aid, arrangement that reveals unseemly symbiotic relationship between higher learning and finance; calls for provision forcing universities with large endowments to spend at least 8 percent annually for educational purposes. ", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "23", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Victor", "role": "reported", "lastname": "FLEISCHER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By VICTOR FLEISCHER"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/19/opinion/stop-universities-from-hoarding-money.html", "lead_paragraph": "They pay lavish fees to manage their wealth, while tuition keeps rising.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Stop Colleges From Hoarding Cash", "main": "Stop Universities From Hoarding Money", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "55d42e6338f0d825c7c2ca5c", "word_count": "899", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/08/19/opinion/19Fleischer/19Fleischer-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/08/19/opinion/19Fleischer/19Fleischer-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 709, "url": "images/2015/08/19/opinion/19Fleischer/19Fleischer-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/08/19/opinion/19Fleischer/19Fleischer-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "709"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/08/19/opinion/19Fleischer/19Fleischer-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2015/08/